# TypeScript and React Patterns

## Component Structure
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Define proper prop interfaces
- Use proper type annotations
- Implement proper error handling
- Use proper state management
- Keep components focused and small

## TypeScript Best Practices
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Define proper interfaces and types
- Use proper type guards
- Implement proper error types
- Use proper generics
- NEVER use `any` prefer `unknown` or generic types

## React Patterns
- Use proper hooks
- Implement proper state management
- Use proper context
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper memoization
- Keep components pure
- Avoid using `useEffect` when possible

## File Organization
- Keep related code together
- Use proper file naming
- Implement proper exports
- Use proper imports
- Keep types close to usage
- Use proper barrel exports
